# Anti-Patterns

What NOT to do in {{SITE_NAME}}. Every item here has caused real problems — either in this project or in similar Astro projects.

Generated by `astro-builder`. See also `docs/astro-patterns.md` for the canonical Astro 6 anti-patterns.

---

## Astro 6 anti-patterns (always forbidden)

These apply to every project using this plugin:

| Anti-pattern | Correct alternative |
|---|---|
| `src/content/config.ts` | `src/content.config.ts` |
| `astro.config.mjs` | `astro.config.ts` |
| Separate collection per language | Single collection with locale subfolders |
| Fixed `category` enum | `tags: string[]` |
| UI strings hardcoded in `.astro` | `tl('key')` from locale JSON |
| Logic or data fetching in page files | Move to page-view |
| `lang` or `tl` passed as props | Each component calls `createTranslator(Astro.currentLocale)` |
| Parsing `Astro.url` for locale | `Astro.currentLocale` |
| `prefixDefaultLocale: false` | `prefixDefaultLocale: true` |
| `redirectToDefaultLocale: true` | `false` + explicit `redirects: { '/': '/en' }` |
| ESLint or Prettier | Biome |
| `npm` or `yarn` | `pnpm` |
| Custom sitemap code | `@astrojs/sitemap` |
| Relative imports across `src/` | Path aliases (`@lib/`, `@components/`, etc.) |
| `// @ts-ignore` in new code | Fix the actual type error |

