## When you encounter an anti-pattern

1. Do not work around it — fix the root cause.
2. Run `pnpm build` and `tsc --noEmit` after fixing to confirm no regressions.
3. If the anti-pattern is in code you did not write and fixing it is out of scope, note it in your report and create a follow-up task.

Never use `--no-verify` to skip git hooks. Never suppress TypeScript errors with `any` or `@ts-ignore` unless the existing codebase already does so in that specific context.
